#circuitbreakersg day 38

MY FAV Pandan sweetmeat. Kanom Krok Bai Toey. Had this in Bangkok and I fell in love with it ever since. It’s a type of Kueh and it is usually seen in flower shape in Bkk. It is so fragrant and it is chewier when less cooked. Best to eat it hot. 
RECIPE:
All purpose flour 130g
Tapioca flour 65g
Baking powder 1 teaspoon
Sugar 85g
A pinch of salt
1 egg
Coconut milk 125ml
coconut pandan juice 240ml (15 pandan leaves + water 250ml, blend and strain) 
Vegetable oil 1 tablespoon

You can cook whatever shape you want🤣 easier to form shapes if you use drizzle bottle or even better if you have the flower mould or takoyaki pan.

Do tag me your creation if you have tried the recipe @jxeats!
